@leaf94 Injected dependencies are initialized after the constructor of the class is called. I need the injected dependencies for initializing these classes and so it needs to happen after the DeploymentService instance is initialized.
@shaguptashaikh Injecting these dependencies means creating these objects in Kernel. I do not prefer that. In addition to above, the constructor you are referring to is not used by Kernel to initialize the service. So this needs to be done explicitly.
I am not super happy with this and willing to revisit how DI works.

